Bases that Y4 reuses (each shipping under its own license; not redistributed
in this repository — pulled in via `third_party/` git submodules or, for
LLVM scudo, via the on-demand vendoring described in
`third_party/scudo/README.md`):

  * seL4 microkernel       https://sel4.systems/
                           (BSD-2-Clause, formally verified)
                           pinned: 15.0.0     (`third_party/sel4/`)
  * Limine bootloader      https://limine-bootloader.org/
                           (BSD-2-Clause)
                           pinned: v12.1.0    (`third_party/limine/`)
  * LLVM scudo standalone  https://llvm.org/
                           (Apache-2.0 with LLVM exception)
                           pinned via SHA in `third_party/scudo/PIN.toml`,
                           materialised by `just scudo-fetch`
                           (vendored on demand — sidesteps the 175k-file
                           git index a full llvm-project submodule incurs)
  * Tock OS (capsule model — design + selected crates)
                           https://tockos.org/
                           (MIT OR Apache-2.0)
  * DragonFlyBSD (LWKT msgport, lock-free SLAB — algorithmic port)
                           https://www.dragonflybsd.org/
                           (BSD-3-Clause)
                           read-only reference at
                           /home/ybi/y4-upstream-refs/dragonfly/
  * Redox OS (scheme IPC dispatcher — algorithmic port)
                           https://www.redox-os.org/
                           (MIT)
                           read-only reference at
                           /home/ybi/y4-upstream-refs/redox-kernel/

Verification toolchain (build-time, not redistributed):

